               <head>Tarjumah-’i Khulāṣat al-mafākhir</head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh2010115021 http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85089073 http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85109389">
                  <summary>A translation by by an anonymous disciple of <persName role="oth" key="person_f1684">Jalāl al-Dīn Bukhārī</persName> (جلال الدین
							بخاری) of Uc̲h̲h, known as Makhdūm-i Jahāniyān (d. 1384) of biographical
							anecdotes largely about <persName role="subject" key="viaf_71359982">ʻAbd al-Qādir Jilānī</persName> (عبد القادر جلانى), written as a
							supplement to the Arabic work <title key="work_7725">Rawḍ al-rayāḥīn fī
								ḥikāyāt al-Ṣāliḥīn</title> by <persName role="aut" key="viaf_102404336">Yāfiʻī, ʻAbd Allāh ibn Asʻad, d.
								1367</persName> (يافعی، عبد الله بن أسعد). 
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_596-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22404">Tarjumah-’i Khulāṣat al-mafākhir </title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">ترجمهٔ خلاصة المفاخر</title>
                     <colophon>Folio 235v: Completed 26 Muḥarram 1031 (10 December 1621) in
								Dacca (Dhākah) for Miyān Sīdū(?). </colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Contents listed on ff. 3r-4v. </p>
                        <p>Followed at the end by some sayings of ʻAbd al-Qādir (ff.
									235v-236r). </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
